{"_id": "QGmr1iNjr5DRbuGn", "name": "Adventure Introduction", "pages": [{"_id": "j3IW4pVsIoYHxsEx", "name": "Adventure Introduction", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<p>The Haunt is a one-shot D&D 5e horror adventure for 4th-5th level characters (3-5 players). Milestone leveling: start at level 4, advance to level 5 upon defeating Gertrude.<br><br>Recommended atmosphere: dim/candle lighting, spooky organ music, creepy children's lullaby on standby.<br><br>Background: General Oscar Montarthas was the last commander of a militia that once protected a small city from orc attacks. He employed an advisor named Gertrude \u2014 who was in fact an evil Night Hag. She seduced him and corrupted his heart with the Leacher's Emerald, drained the manor's residents, then the city's population. The city fell to orcs and was abandoned. The manor alone survives, and Gertrude has fed from travelers ever since.</p>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_intro", "type": "dm_notes", "floor": "none", "area_number": 0}}}
{"_id": "yztX7tSxPn8iUegn", "name": "1. Manor Entryway", "pages": [{"_id": "CINPnUiiDcn1Q4YO", "name": "1. Manor Entryway", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83d\udcd6 Read Aloud</h3><blockquote><em>You stand in near darkness. Before you are a set of steps that lead to the high archways that govern the entryway into the mansion proper. A large set of dark oak double doors sit patiently closed awaiting your advance. You notice small crystal blue eyes peering at you from behind a dark window beside the doorway.</em></blockquote><h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Doors are supernaturally sealed. No check opens them. They open on their own once heroes turn away or have tried for more than a few minutes.<br><br>DC 13 INT (Arcana): detects eerie essence around the doors.<br><br>Once they turn away: 'As you turn from the door you hear a loud creeeeaaak from behind you...' Read full boxed text. The crystal blue eyes \u2014 see Area 3 (the evil doll on the couch).</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Doors immune to Strength and Thieves Tools checks</li><li>Open automatically when party turns away or waits ~5 minutes</li><li>DC 13 INT Arcana detects supernatural sealing</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area1", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 1}}}
{"_id": "TsfJASld7S49gNid", "name": "2. The Foyer", "pages": [{"_id": "0PxXZPkqM6Igb6Q4", "name": "2. The Foyer", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83d\udcd6 Read Aloud</h3><blockquote><em>The entry foyer has a large open space with a floor of black marble. Two imposing looking demonic statues stand to either side of the foyer as if motionlessly keeping watch over the empty room.</em></blockquote><h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>TRAPPED ROOM. Trap triggers when a living soul crosses the line between the two statues (see map \u2014 the gargoyle trigger line is between them).<br><br>Both gargoyles (MM p.140) animate immediately. Fight to the death.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Trigger: crossing line between the two gargoyle statues</li><li>Both gargoyles animate on trigger</li><li>Fight to the death</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area2", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 2}}}
{"_id": "ca7L1McaX25V1iG3", "name": "3. The Stairwell Waiting Room", "pages": [{"_id": "WjH3GtOPkG1wdabp", "name": "3. The Stairwell Waiting Room", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Raised platform (step up from foyer and tea room). Situated at the bottom of the stairwell.<br><br>Features:<br>- SW corner: cushioned couch with old worn children's doll. DC 10 Investigation: doll's eyes are the same crystal blue eyes seen at the front door.<br>- NE corner: stairwell up to Second Floor OR down to Basement. Portcullis blocks the way UP until party has explored 5+ ground floor rooms \u2014 then opens by itself.<br>- Griffon statue on pedestal to right of stairwell. Holding front talon up in a 'knocking' stance.<br><br>GRIFFON MECHANISM (S1 \u2014 Secret Door System 1): Pulling down the griffon's raised talon activates 2 secret doors. One opens while the other closes, and vice versa. Neither door can be open simultaneously. Trigger must be pulled from outside the secret passage (Area 8). Designed to split the party.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Portcullis to upper floor: locked until 5 ground floor rooms explored</li><li>S1 Griffon lever: controls both Area 4 (tea room) secret door and Area 8 entry door \u2014 one open at a time</li><li>Children's doll: DC 10 Investigation connects eyes to front door</li><li>Portcullis to basement: always accessible</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area3", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 3}}}
{"_id": "wBS5zK9LhHQWW9rx", "name": "4. The Tea Room", "pages": [{"_id": "NxxFEQ7WokY0g2nl", "name": "4. The Tea Room", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Large sunken room. NW corner: fireplace and hearth. Three small round tables for refreshments. Glass chandelier on chain.<br><br>EVENT: As heroes move through, chandelier falls and crashes JUST BEHIND them. Chain swings. Alarming but not lethal.<br><br>S1 SECRET DOOR: In the wall connecting to Area 8 (Secret Passage). Activated by the griffon talon lever in Area 3. When first entered, it looks like a wall. DC 13 WIS Perception to spot it.<br><br>Open entrance to Area 5 (Dining Room) \u2014 not a door.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Chandelier fall event: flavor/scare, no damage</li><li>S1 secret door: DC 13 WIS Perception to spot</li><li>Activated only from Area 3 griffon lever</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area4", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 4}}}
{"_id": "su7oudgJfmpOa88Y", "name": "5. The Dining Room", "pages": [{"_id": "r689PuGhf72KL586", "name": "5. The Dining Room", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83d\udcd6 Read Aloud</h3><blockquote><em>As you step up into the dining room from the sunken tea room, the air grows warm. Suddenly the room comes to life, as ghostly apparitions appear seated at the once empty table. A large dinner party is being held it seems, as a roasted hog materialises, along with plates of all varieties of food. Jugs of foaming ale are being shared between ghostly companions. A large spectral human man stands at the head of the table, saying nothing, a serious scowl and frown is cemented over his face as he overlooks his guests who seem to be enjoying themselves.</em></blockquote><h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Open entrance from tea room \u2014 raised up steps from sunken tea room.<br><br>Ghosts appear on first entry and ignore the party unless interacted with.<br><br>IF INTERACTED WITH: Room goes quiet. Every ghost turns toward party. Man at head of table rushes through the dining table: 'You should not be here! LEAVE THIS PLACE!!!!' Then everything vanishes \u2014 room cold and empty again.<br><br>IF PARTY LINGERS 5+ MINUTES: Room catches phantom fire. DC 15 WIS save each round \u2014 fail: 1d4 psychic damage. Flames disappear when party leaves. No burns, nothing burnt.<br><br>Ghosts and flames are apparitions \u2014 no combat stat blocks.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Ghostly dinner party: apparitions only, no combat stats</li><li>Interaction triggers general's warning and disappearance</li><li>Lingering 5+ min: phantom fire, DC 15 WIS save or 1d4 psychic per round</li><li>All effects end when party leaves the room</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area5", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 5}}}
{"_id": "osA6ZkdH5Wk2Au3W", "name": "6. The Ballroom", "pages": [{"_id": "kWtaooCYthX9Purc", "name": "6. The Ballroom", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83d\udcd6 Read Aloud</h3><blockquote><em>As you enter the large double doors, a large room opens before you. A large chandelier hangs from the high ceiling, and an old dance floor stretches before you. A large glass folding door opens onto an alfresco area on the east wall.\n\nMaterializing from thin air you see the man who had rushed at you, ending the ghostly dinner party in the dining room. He seems younger somehow, as if this is a vision into an earlier time in his life.\n\nA beautiful woman enters from nothingness, dressed in a flowing black gown, her eyes dark and dangerous. He holds her and looks into those eyes, and she looks back into his.\n\n'We will disappear, just the two of us, my love' the man says dreamily.\n\n'Oh, General Montharthas, but what of your wife? And we have work to do.' She reminds him.\n\n'Never mind her, she will cope. And your army of undead... Let us not talk of this tonight' he replies as their apparitions fade and the room is once again empty.</em></blockquote><h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Lore scene only \u2014 no combat, no loot. Reveals General Montarthas and Gertrude's relationship. East glass doors lead to Area 7 (Alfresco).</p>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area6", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 6}}}
{"_id": "GEescujQHaMCaKFo", "name": "7. Alfresco Area", "pages": [{"_id": "ucLFTfhCO7MKCgdH", "name": "7. Alfresco Area", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Fenced outdoor pool area. Three ruined deck chairs at south end. Pool water is still and algae green. Ripples occasionally break the surface. Multiple skeletal remains around near poolside.<br><br>DC 13 WIS Passive Perception: notices a gleaming bejeweled sword on the far deck (marked X on map).<br><br>BEHOLDER ZOMBIE ENCOUNTER: Triggered when party gets within 5ft of poolside OR attempts to retrieve the sword. Beholder Zombie (MM p.316) rises from the pool. Does not leave the alfresco area.<br><br>LOOT (after defeating zombie): Level 4 avg \u2192 any +1 magic weapon party lacks. Level 5 avg \u2192 Flame Tongue longsword (DMG p.170).</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>DC 13 WIS Passive Perception to notice sword</li><li>Beholder Zombie rises from pool: triggered by coming within 5ft of poolside or reaching for sword</li><li>Beholder Zombie confined to alfresco area</li><li>Sword: +1 weapon (lvl 4 party) or Flame Tongue (lvl 5 party)</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area7", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 7}}}
{"_id": "iCFjUwG9plBWm0GK", "name": "8. The Secret Passage", "pages": [{"_id": "LXKeWmd8gLy8upOl", "name": "8. The Secret Passage", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Bare stone room. Doors at both ends can ONLY be opened/closed by the griffon talon lever in Area 3. One door open at a time \u2014 when one opens, the other closes. Lever must be pulled from outside the passage, meaning it requires two party members to get someone through to the other side. Designed intentionally to split the party and create tension.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Both doors controlled by griffon lever in Area 3</li><li>Only one door open at a time</li><li>Lever must be operated from outside passage</li><li>Requires coordination of two party members</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area8", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 8}}}
{"_id": "OYlSasBFECxATCgz", "name": "9. Empty Thoroughfare", "pages": [{"_id": "Ci4dGzte6p57MttC", "name": "9. Empty Thoroughfare", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Empty corridor. Provides walkway through the wizard's quarters for those who know the manor's secret ways. No encounters, no loot.</p>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area9", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 9}}}
{"_id": "2gwoSPc5F7wyk2mo", "name": "10. The Wizard's Bedroom", "pages": [{"_id": "2OXNXdjmYBAVVkb1", "name": "10. The Wizard's Bedroom", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>20x20ft room. Old rotted wooden bed on south side. Old desk on west side.<br><br>DC 10 WIS Perception reveals:<br>1. Scroll of Invisibility (DC 10 INT Arcana confirms magical preservation)<br>2. Page from ancient journal (DC 13 WIS Perception: touching makes it crumble to dust)<br><br>JOURNAL PAGE TEXT:<br>12th day of Mirtul: 'Today the General meets with his new advisor, she comes highly regarded!...'<br>14th day of Mirtul: 'The new advisor Gertrude has only been in our service for two days, and already I see a change in the General...'<br>25th day Mirtul: 'Something is wrong. The General dismisses the Lords...This new advisor holds all of his attention, she feeds him the poison of her words...'<br>30th day of Mirtul: 'Today is the day that I, Marple Brightshine, make a stand for the greater good! She will die by my hand...I see her for what she really is, a night witch!'<br><br>Journal ends with that final entry.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>DC 10 WIS Perception to find scroll and journal</li><li>DC 10 INT Arcana to identify scroll</li><li>DC 13 WIS Perception: touching journal page destroys it</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area10", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 10}}}
{"_id": "j1fci84iUb0Wkmnl", "name": "11. The Spell Practice Room", "pages": [{"_id": "c5uPQi4GF4JzFZrv", "name": "11. The Spell Practice Room", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Large open space. Three stone mannequins along south wall \u2014 practice targets. Large black blast marks on wall behind them. Large iron double doors to Library (Area 12), blackened from fire.<br><br>SECRET DOOR (northern wall): DC 15 WIS Perception to find. DC 15 STR Athletics to open (trigger mechanism destroyed in the fire that burned the library). Provides alternative exit route.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Secret door north wall: DC 15 WIS Perception, DC 15 STR Athletics to force open</li><li>Iron double doors to Area 12</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area11", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 11}}}
{"_id": "VPtHGo932E34h5Dy", "name": "12. The Library", "pages": [{"_id": "NYKcL7tm6oMPCQVV", "name": "12. The Library", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>All four walls badly burnt. Ash and rubble on floor mixed with burnt book remains. Partially hidden piles of humanoid skeletons. Only intact object: leather cloak draped over half-melted metal coat stand.<br><br>CLOAKER: The leather cloak IS a Cloaker (MM p.41). DC 16 INT Nature to recognize before triggering.<br><br>ENCOUNTER: Once heroes cross the threshold into the room, the Cloaker surprises them (if not detected). Attacks until 5 HP remaining, then flees to another part of the wizard's quarters to surprise the party again later (DM discretion).</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>DC 16 INT Nature to identify Cloaker before it strikes</li><li>Cloaker surprises party on entry (if undetected)</li><li>Retreats at 5 HP to strike again later</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area12", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 12}}}
{"_id": "jCxeZHmpkZ0YeQhZ", "name": "13. Escape Preparation Room", "pages": [{"_id": "wur76nk2ixhyALiN", "name": "13. Escape Preparation Room", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Secret room. Preparation/escape staging area for the General and his Wizard. Four faded black cloaks with hoods hanging on hooks. Door leads to the courtyard garden (Area 14). No encounters, no loot beyond the cloaks.</p>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area13", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 13}}}
{"_id": "FBnPVEBIFIJqNXBm", "name": "14. The Courtyard", "pages": [{"_id": "K0mEKvVDoIugvXi4", "name": "14. The Courtyard", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Outdoor courtyard garden. Lined with shrubs and hedge bushes. NE corner: hidden hatch through shrubs and outer wall \u2014 escape route to the field beyond (not featured in this adventure). DC 13 WIS Perception to notice the hatch.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>DC 13 WIS Perception to find hidden escape hatch in NE corner</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area14", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 14}}}
{"_id": "zG8hXSBtp09kwhcJ", "name": "15. The Basement", "pages": [{"_id": "4gYqWbDp9pM40PFn", "name": "15. The Basement", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83d\udcd6 Read Aloud</h3><blockquote><em>You enter the room, and suddenly the door slams shut behind you. A locking mechanism with a 4 digit code blocks the way and green noxious gas begins to fill the room.\n\nIn the room you see a half made flesh golem lying on an operating table, it is missing only hands, feet and a brain. A large mechanism with a crank and coils sits behind it with rods connected to each of the golem's temples.\n\nTo the left of the golem are three large buckets holding many feet, hands, and brains. Some rusty operating tools and a needle and thread sit on the table next to it.\n\nTo the right of the golem sits a desk with a waxed scrap of paper that looks to be a diagram of a humanoid body. It has notes scribbled all over it.</em></blockquote><h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>PUZZLE ROOM \u2014 ESCAPE THE GAS.<br><br>Door slams on entry. 4-digit code lock. Noxious green gas fills the room.<br><br>STEP 1 \u2014 SOLVE NUMBER SEQUENCES (determines correct body parts):<br>- Hands: 2, 7, 3, 8, ? \u2192 Answer: 4 (sequence +5, -4, +5, -4)<br>- Feet: 3, 12, 6, 24, ? \u2192 Answer: 12 (sequence x4, /2, x4, /2)<br>- Brain: 8, 16, 22, 44, ? \u2192 Answer: 50 (sequence x2, +6, x2, +6)<br>Give players the Flesh Golem Handout.<br><br>STEP 2 \u2014 ATTACH BODY PARTS:<br>DC 13 INT Medicine check for each of the 3 parts. If party fails 3 total checks: gas renders them unconscious \u2192 wake in Area 24.<br><br>STEP 3 \u2014 ACTIVATE THE GOLEM:<br>DC 15 INT Arcana to realize: either start the crank mechanism OR cast a lightning-based spell.<br><br>RESULT: Golem uses the inserted brain's memories to push the 4-digit door code and open the door. Gas clears.<br><br>FAILURE FALLBACK: If unsolved in 20 real-time minutes, gas knocks party unconscious. They wake in Area 24 (A General's Broken Heart). Run that scene as written.<br><br>LOOT: Bag of Holding (DMG p.153).</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Gas trap: door seals on entry</li><li>Sequence puzzle: Hands=4, Feet=12, Brain=50</li><li>DC 13 INT Medicine per body part attachment (3 fails = unconscious)</li><li>DC 15 INT Arcana to activate golem (or lightning spell)</li><li>20-minute real-time fail: unconscious, wake in Area 24</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area15", "type": "room", "floor": "ground", "area_number": 15}}}
{"_id": "o642NKj8Q35DoVtL", "name": "16. The Hallway (2nd Floor)", "pages": [{"_id": "kfED9XZn7Fu10ABh", "name": "16. The Hallway (2nd Floor)", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Soft green glow flickering in the hallway with no apparent source. DC 15 INT Arcana: the green glow is necrotic energy moving through the manor's second floor like blood through a vein.<br><br>EVIL DOLL: 40% chance of appearance in each room on 2nd floor. Roll d% on entry to every room. If doll appears, use the Evil Doll Appearances table \u2014 track which appearance number this is.<br><br>Evil Doll Appearances:<br>1st: Sitting on furniture, does nothing until party leaves, then Frightening Lullaby + Claw attack. Shadow Blend on 2nd turn.<br>2nd: Turns head slowly with evil grin, attacks with Knife. Shadow Blend on turn 2 to escape.<br>3rd: Shadow Blend surprise attack, drops from shadows onto a PC with Knife. Fights until Shadow Blend recharges, then escapes. Reappears later at DM discretion.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>40% chance Evil Doll per 2nd floor room entry</li><li>DC 15 INT Arcana: identifies necrotic energy source</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area16", "type": "room", "floor": "second", "area_number": 16}}}
{"_id": "AqLmGanAbJJvYE64", "name": "17. Guest Rooms (2nd Floor)", "pages": [{"_id": "IB4DwI4HR7hl8XyV", "name": "17. Guest Rooms (2nd Floor)", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Two standard guest rooms \u2014 both dusty and full of sticky cobwebs.<br><br>On entry to EITHER guest room, roll 1d20. EVEN result: 2x Phase Spiders (MM p.334) phase in from above the doorway and attack.<br><br>40% Evil Doll chance also applies.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Roll 1d20 on entry \u2014 even result triggers 2 Phase Spiders</li><li>Phase Spiders attack from above doorway</li><li>40% Evil Doll chance</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area17", "type": "room", "floor": "second", "area_number": 17}}}
{"_id": "IcVFzeq8KzAE8e4K", "name": "18. The Laundry Room (2nd Floor)", "pages": [{"_id": "HWX719QK7LLHuERN", "name": "18. The Laundry Room (2nd Floor)", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Old laundry room. Bench runs along south wall. Large iron stirring pot for washing clothes. A ghostly apparition stirs an ectoplasmic load of dirty clothes. The ghost fades when party attempts to interact OR enters the room.<br><br>No combat. 40% Evil Doll chance.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Ghostly laundress: fades on interaction or entry</li><li>40% Evil Doll chance</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area18", "type": "room", "floor": "second", "area_number": 18}}}
{"_id": "UqM0ulsdNqJNloAa", "name": "19. The Guests Wash Room (2nd Floor)", "pages": [{"_id": "H2Sqd7iCMmf7iId3", "name": "19. The Guests Wash Room (2nd Floor)", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83d\udcd6 Read Aloud</h3><blockquote><em>As you enter what looks to be an old washroom, you first notice the bloodied towel hanging from the towel rack. A wash tub sits along the northern wall of the room. Then you notice it; a naked body lies within the otherwise empty tub, blood gushing from the woman's wrists.</em></blockquote><h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Large washing tub. Bench along SW corner. Old bloodied towel on towel rack.<br><br>GHOST ENCOUNTER: The body in the tub is a Ghost (MM p.147). Attacks ONLY if heroes attempt to interact with it or 'save' it. Otherwise it is passive.<br><br>40% Evil Doll chance.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Ghost only hostile if party interacts with it</li><li>40% Evil Doll chance</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area19", "type": "room", "floor": "second", "area_number": 19}}}
{"_id": "ECX7vmeNtvOTZhMM", "name": "20. The Servant's Living Space (2nd Floor)", "pages": [{"_id": "EtnBchn6hVmFHSMN", "name": "20. The Servant's Living Space (2nd Floor)", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>As party approaches from hallway, they hear THUMPING growing louder as they near.<br><br>BEHIND LOCKED DOOR: 1 Ghast (MM p.148) commanding 2 Ghouls (MM p.148). They can smell living flesh, are frenzied with hunger \u2014 neither party is surprised when door opens. They fight to the death.<br><br>DOOR: Locked for a very long time. DC 15 DEX Thieves Tools to unlock.<br><br>ROOM: Old servant's living quarters. North-east sub-room: shared lavatory. South-east sub-room: shared bathing area.<br><br>40% Evil Doll chance.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Door locked: DC 15 DEX Thieves Tools</li><li>Thumping audible before entering</li><li>No surprise for either side</li><li>All undead fight to death</li><li>40% Evil Doll chance</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area20", "type": "room", "floor": "second", "area_number": 20}}}
{"_id": "VAbVjvmnw5jCIN3B", "name": "21. The Kitchen (2nd Floor)", "pages": [{"_id": "5RlgNhve4f5YspIe", "name": "21. The Kitchen (2nd Floor)", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Hotplate with fire-pit, unused for millennia. Bench on south wall. Wooden cupboards on all sides. Pots, pans, knives, cups on hooks below cupboards. South wall: hole in floor (dumbwaiter shaft, big enough for a medium creature).<br><br>TREASURE VISIBLE ON ENTRY: Small locked chest on the hotplate across the room. DC 15 DEX Thieves Tools OR DC 13 STR Athletics to open.<br><br>IT'S A TRAP: DC 15 WIS Perception on entry notices cold air and cupboard doors moving slightly.<br><br>POLTERGEIST ENCOUNTER: As party reaches halfway across the kitchen, knives, pots, and pans slowly detach from hooks. Cupboards start flinging open/closed viciously, hurling objects across the room.<br><br>Each cupboard: AC 10, 10 HP. Destroying 4 cupboards destroys the Poltergeist.<br><br>COMBAT: Roll initiative when objects detach. Each hero inside the room makes DC 13 DEX save at start of their turn \u2014 fail: 1d6 bludgeoning + slashing damage.<br><br>LOOT: Chest contains 248 gp (unknown origin).<br><br>40% Evil Doll chance.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>DC 15 WIS Perception: detects trap before triggered</li><li>Poltergeist triggered at halfway across room</li><li>Cupboards: AC 10, 10 HP each \u2014 destroy 4 to end encounter</li><li>DC 13 DEX save each turn inside kitchen or 1d6 bludgeoning+slashing</li><li>Chest: DC 15 Thieves Tools or DC 13 Athletics</li><li>40% Evil Doll chance</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area21", "type": "room", "floor": "second", "area_number": 21}}}
{"_id": "mvnQMscy5aiJk5Mc", "name": "22. The General's Clerk (2nd Floor)", "pages": [{"_id": "3HKUjXx6xOe0vZiI", "name": "22. The General's Clerk (2nd Floor)", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83d\udcd6 Read Aloud</h3><blockquote><em>As you enter the room you notice something that seems very unnatural, though not unexpected in a place such as this. It is a skeleton busy at work behind a writing desk, frantically writing notes in an translucent ethereal ledger book.\n\nIt looks up at you with empty eye sockets, its jaw starts to move as a hauntingly high pitched voice says 'ahh, you are here! He has been waiting for you!... You may proceed Advisor Gertrude!'\n\nFrom behind, you feel something evil and dark trespass through your bodies, as the aspect of a dangerously beautiful woman with dark and deadly eyes walks straight through you, a smirk on her ghostly smile. She walks straight through the closed door and disappears, while the skeleton clerk goes back to his duties.</em></blockquote><h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Skeleton clerk at writing desk (SW corner). Single door on east wall.<br><br>Skeleton: Ignores the party completely. If physically interacted with, it falls limp and crumbles to ash.<br><br>Gertrude's aspect passes through the party into the next room \u2014 this is the vision that leads to Area 23 and eventually Area 24.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Skeleton clerk: non-hostile, crumbles to ash if touched</li><li>Vision of Gertrude passing through party</li><li>Door to Area 23 on east wall</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area22", "type": "room", "floor": "second", "area_number": 22}}}
{"_id": "5chSk2lZmRBPIzXp", "name": "23. The General's Waiting Room (2nd Floor)", "pages": [{"_id": "o552JTAFWGIVEXCT", "name": "23. The General's Waiting Room (2nd Floor)", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83d\udcd6 Read Aloud</h3><blockquote><em>As you look around the room, it appears empty at first, but within the blink of an eye, a small pretty girl, no more than 5 or 6, is suddenly sitting on the long bench that stretches the northern wall. She seems to be waiting patiently. The dark and deadly looking woman appears in the room, smiles at the child, and offers her a children's doll. The girl smiles with joy as the woman evaporates. The child's smile turns to pain and anguish as blood soaked stab wounds begin to appear on her silky white dress. She falls limp and tumbles to the floor before disappearing. You notice that the doll is left lying on the bench, a knife in its hand and a grin on its face.</em></blockquote><h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>Extended waiting room. Bench along north wall. South wall: large oak double doors carved with a tree motif \u2014 names of all generals who served at the manor, earliest at top, latest at bottom. Last name: 'General Oscar Montarthas.' No more.<br><br>EVIL DOLL ENCOUNTER: After the vision, if the doll has NOT been defeated in a final confrontation yet, the doll attacks \u2014 fighting until 5 HP remaining, then Shadow Blend to escape. If already defeated earlier, the doll in this scene is just an apparition and disappears if touched.<br><br>DOOR TO AREA 24: Although unlocked, it's stuck from the other side. DC 13 STR Athletics to open. On opening, party sees a large heavy chest has been wedged against it from inside.<br><br>LOOT: Chest contains 12 iron bars @ 1 gp each.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>Vision plays out automatically on entry</li><li>Evil Doll encounter (if not previously defeated) after vision</li><li>Door stuck: DC 13 STR Athletics</li><li>Large chest against door from inside</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area23", "type": "room", "floor": "second", "area_number": 23}}}
{"_id": "6B8EZeetzFvVlhE7", "name": "24. A General's Broken Heart (2nd Floor)", "pages": [{"_id": "WGqC1h3ogdNPLkgr", "name": "24. A General's Broken Heart (2nd Floor)", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<h3>\ud83d\udcd6 Read Aloud \u2014 Doors Open</h3><blockquote><em>As soon as you hear the doors slam shut from behind, a great gust of wind blasts the room around you; sending dust, paper and curtains flying around the room. Piles of rotting corpses litter the creaky wooden floor.\n\nThen you see him, on the ceiling, a shell of a man, shriveled, tortured and used. His body and arms semi moulded into the blackened muck that replicates a ceiling. Slimy black vines creep through his flesh pinning him to the ceiling, as the ends of the vines expand into drooling suckers that feed from his life force.\n\nA glow of green hue emanates from his chest where a green emerald spews out evil energies into the mansion distributing the feed to all areas of the living building. The most potent looking of these green energies flows directly into a lifeless body slumped with its head flung back over a wooden chair.</em></blockquote><h3>\ud83d\udcd6 Read Aloud \u2014 Gertrude Reveals Herself</h3><blockquote><em>The body snaps its head back from over the chair and back into position. You recognise her from the apparitions of the manor. It is the dark advisor Gertrude. She grins wide and evil, then cackles a haunting laugh as her features grow long and haggard. Her skin turns midnight blue and her pupils turn the red of the 9 hells. She attacks!</em></blockquote><h3>\ud83c\udfb2 DM Notes</h3><p>FINAL BOSS ROOM.<br><br>DOOR PULL: Each hero makes DC 17 STR save or is pulled involuntarily into the room. If ALL pass (very unlikely), only the lowest roll is pulled in anyway.<br><br>PARTY SPLIT: Heroes who resist must bash down the door (AC 13, 40 HP) to help their comrade inside.<br><br>GENERAL ON CEILING: General Montarthas is pinned to the ceiling by black vines, Leacher's Emerald in his chest feeding Gertrude.<br><br>GERTRUDE ENCOUNTER: See actor_gertrude for full stat block and tactics.<br><br>AFTER GERTRUDE DIES: Vines wither. General falls to floor. Breathes shallowly, smiles, whispers 'thank you,' disintegrates to ash. Only the Leacher's Emerald remains.<br><br>DC 13 INT Arcana: identifies emerald's necrotic energy and reveals its properties.<br><br>MANOR COLLAPSE: After the fight (or if party lingers), the manor begins to shake and collapse.<br>- Building falls in: after party moves through 3 more rooms, OR if they linger too long<br>- Every 15ft moved: DC 13 DEX save or 1d10 bludgeoning from debris<br>- After 8 saves: manor falls. Any hero inside takes 1d100+10 bludgeoning damage.</p><h3>\u2699\ufe0f Mechanics</h3><ul><li>DC 17 STR save to resist being pulled in (lowest roll still goes in)</li><li>Door: AC 13, 40 HP for those outside</li><li>Gertrude combat: see full tactics in actor_gertrude</li><li>Post-combat: manor begins collapsing</li><li>Collapse: DC 13 DEX per 15ft moved, 1d10 on fail</li><li>After 8 saves: 1d100+10 auto damage if still inside</li></ul>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_area24", "type": "room", "floor": "second", "area_number": 24}}}
{"_id": "ZW6RD8QuRzaF0rDn", "name": "Epilogue", "pages": [{"_id": "PqShaBdnCJozWUnd", "name": "Epilogue", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<p>TWO ENDINGS:<br><br>IF EVIL DOLL SURVIVED: The manor collapses. Gertrude defeated. As dawn approaches, party notices a pair of glowing crystal blue eyes in the surrounding woods \u2014 followed by a horrifying girlish giggle that fades into darkness. The Evil Doll lives on as a potential recurring villain.<br><br>IF EVIL DOLL DEFEATED: Clean ending. Manor falls to rubble. Both Gertrude and the Evil Doll are gone. The undead are at rest. Dawn comes. It's going to be a better day.</p>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_epilogue", "type": "dm_notes", "floor": "none", "area_number": 0}}}
{"_id": "1QtDI5hyCl8AKv17", "name": "Player Handout: Flesh Golem Diagram", "pages": [{"_id": "51OBwmDj17WPG77c", "name": "Player Handout: Flesh Golem Diagram", "type": "text", "text": {"content": "<p>The waxed diagram of a human body with anatomical labels. Scrawled notes read:<br><br>'Solving the formula will tell me which the right parts are!'<br>'The door is locked... I am trapped... Only he knew the code... Now his brain lies in the bucket for my Flesh Golem!'<br>'Not enough time to finish him... I do not want to die!'<br><br>Number sequences:<br>Hands: 2, 7, 3, 8, ?<br>Feet: 3, 12, 6, 24, ?<br>Brain: 8, 16, 22, 44, ?<br><br>'Three more body parts to complete him!'<br>'He will open it for me!'</p>", "format": 1}, "image": {}, "video": {}, "src": null, "system": {}, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}], "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {"questwright": {"id": "journal_handout_flesh_golem", "type": "player_handout", "floor": "none", "area_number": 0}}}
